# Vercel deploy workflow

This project deploys via Vercel Git integration (push to `main` → production deploy). There is no local Vercel CLI requirement.

After completing a batch of user-requested code changes:

1. Ensure changes are committed with a clear message (commit when the user asked for work to be done or explicitly asked to deploy).
2. Push to `origin/main` with `git push`.
3. Tell the user the push was made and that Vercel will deploy automatically (usually 1–2 minutes).
4. If the user only asked to deploy, commit any uncommitted work first, then push.

Do not force-push. Do not skip git hooks.

